Dialogue: 10,0:00:41.44,0:00:46.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Matsuyama in Shikoku... \NThat's pretty far away, isn't it?
Dialogue: 10,0:00:47.57,0:00:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, pretty far.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:49.32,0:00:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,What part of Japan is it?
Dialogue: 10,0:00:51.48,0:00:52.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The west.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:53.70,0:00:55.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it closer than Hakone?
Dialogue: 10,0:00:56.60,0:00:58.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course not! It's {\i1}way{\i0} past.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:59.75,0:01:01.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:02.55,0:01:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you really need to go \Nway out there to teach?
Dialogue: 10,0:01:06.42,0:01:09.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean... I have to, but only for one term.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:09.47,0:01:12.13,Default,,0,0,0,,When summer vacation starts next year, I'll be back.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:13.81,0:01:17.28,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Kiyo had been my family's servant since before I was born.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:17.95,0:01:18.72,Narrator,,0,0,0,,And...
Dialogue: 10,0:01:19.32,0:01:22.44,Narrator,,0,0,0,,I don't know why, \Nbut she took great care of me.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:22.44,0:01:24.06,Narrator,,0,0,0,,I liked her too.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:29.81,0:01:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,This may be the last time I see you.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:33.14,0:01:35.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Take care of yourself.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:35.82,0:01:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop talking like that, Kiyo!
Dialogue: 10,0:01:38.10,0:01:41.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be back soon,\N and then I'll move back in.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:41.41,0:01:44.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Botchan, write to me as soon \Nas you get to Matsuyama.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:45.26,0:01:46.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. Got it.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:51.81,0:01:54.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Goodbye, Kiyo. Take care!
Dialogue: 10,0:01:54.94,0:01:56.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You too, Botchan.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:58.08,0:02:02.70,Narrator,,0,0,0,,I thought the train had run far enough for Kiyo to leave already, {lit: I thought it was already okay - w/e he means}
Dialogue: 10,0:02:02.70,0:02:04.60,Narrator,,0,0,0,,so I stuck my head out\N the window to look back.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:05.36,0:02:07.04,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Kiyo was still there.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:07.71,0:02:09.92,Narrator,,0,0,0,,She looked unbelievably tiny.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:47.27,0:02:50.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The teachers must be ready by now. Follow me.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:01.38,0:03:08.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, everyone, this is our new teacher, sent here all the way from Tokyo.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:08.46,0:03:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,He is a math teacher, who graduated from
Dialogue: 10,0:03:11.30,0:03:14.65,Default,,0,0,0,,the Tokyo School of Physics this year.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:11.96,0:03:14.65,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Kiyo, thanks for seeing me off.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:14.65,0:03:17.77,Narrator,,0,0,0,,I just got here yesterday, \Nand I'm already bored by this place.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:19.51,0:03:23.34,Narrator,,0,0,0,,As soon as I arrived, \NI gave everyone nicknames.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:23.34,0:03:25.18,Narrator,,0,0,0,,I call the principal "Tanuki." {tanuki in your 2020 fansub of the other version of Botchan anime}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:25.83,0:03:28.18,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The vice principal is "Red Shirt."
Dialogue: 10,0:03:25.83,0:03:27.39,Overlap,,0,0,0,,Yes, my pleasure.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:29.05,0:03:31.19,Narrator,,0,0,0,,"Unprepared" teaches English. {uranari}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:31.19,0:03:32.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You're from Tokyo?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:32.92,0:03:34.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Why, that's delightful!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:34.05,0:03:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Small world! \NI am a fellow Tokyoite, you know.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:37.86,0:03:39.69,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The science teacher is "Buffoon." {nodaiko - not really sure what it means in japanese}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:40.03,0:03:41.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Glad you're finally here.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:41.79,0:03:43.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Hotta, the head math teacher.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:45.68,0:03:47.71,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The math teacher is "Porcupine." {yamaarashi}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:48.57,0:03:51.61,Narrator,,0,0,0,,I'll write more later.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:51.61,0:03:52.65,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Goodbye for now.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:02.06,0:04:03.37,Default,,0,0,0,,This room?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:04.47,0:04:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello again. I've come\N to discuss your curriculum.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:10.13,0:04:11.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks for coming all the way here.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:12.28,0:04:14.99,Default,,0,0,0,,We'd like you to start teaching \Nthe day after tomorrow.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:24.20,0:04:27.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You won't be able to afford\N the rent on a place like this.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:28.74,0:04:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me find you a cheaper place.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:31.98,0:04:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yeah, thanks.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:35.60,0:04:38.67,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Porcupine negotiated a deal \Nwith an antique dealer
Dialogue: 10,0:04:38.67,0:04:41.21,Narrator,,0,0,0,,named Ikagin for me \Nto rent a room from him.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:47.34,0:04:49.60,Narrator,,0,0,0,,On the way back, \Nhe treated me to shaved ice.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:50.96,0:04:55.35,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Porcupine seems like a pretty nice guy \Nafter everything he's done for me.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:55.91,0:05:00.44,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Later on, the students told me\N he's the most popular teacher.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:03.94,0:05:05.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you go, ma'am.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:05.32,0:05:06.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:07.66,0:05:09.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll pay for mine.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:09.06,0:05:10.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry about it.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:16.21,0:05:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't get over how gorgeous she is!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:26.52,0:05:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You look like you're raring to go.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:28.52,0:05:30.53,Default,,0,0,0,,N-Not really, I just...
Dialogue: 10,0:05:30.53,0:05:31.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't sweat it!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:31.34,0:05:35.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The first day of class is always a little rough for everyone.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:37.49,0:05:40.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm only saying this once, \Nso pay attention.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:40.53,0:05:44.11,Default,,0,0,0,,First, we determine the magnitude of angle BAC.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:44.11,0:05:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,If side BC is 12 cm, \Nit will be an equilateral triangle.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:47.72,0:05:50.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, angle BAC must be 60 degrees.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:50.90,0:05:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Then take BC as the base and solve for the height of AD.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:55.35,0:05:59.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Do the same with AB and solve for CE, then compare the two.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:59.63,0:06:04.07,Default,,0,0,0,,This is equivalent to the formula for the area of a triangle, so...
Dialogue: 10,0:06:04.07,0:06:05.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Teacher?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:05.07,0:06:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:05.93,0:06:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't understand, \N'cause you talk too fast.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:09.44,0:06:12.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you talk more slower? {speaking with a strong southern provincial accent}
Dialogue: 10,0:06:12.14,0:06:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,"More slower"?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:13.76,0:06:17.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Aye. It's like you're talking some foreign language.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:17.77,0:06:19.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I... I see.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:19.93,0:06:23.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm from Tokyo, so I don't talk with your accent.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:23.07,0:06:26.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Forgive me. I'll try to explain it\N one more time.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:29.98,0:06:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Teacher!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:31.28,0:06:31.74,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:32.06,0:06:36.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't understand this problem. \NCan you explain it?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:36.75,0:06:38.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me see.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:43.84,0:06:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you solve it?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:48.96,0:06:51.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't, can you?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:52.30,0:06:55.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I can't solve it right now. \NWe'll discuss it later.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:57.37,0:06:58.43,Default,,0,0,0,,He can't do it!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:58.86,0:07:00.24,Thought,,0,0,0,,Those idiots!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:00.24,0:07:02.94,Thought,,0,0,0,,Of course there are problems \Neven the teacher can't solve.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:03.26,0:07:05.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The Tokyo teacher can't do it!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:10.52,0:07:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! How was your first class?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:13.04,0:07:14.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it went okay.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:15.54,0:07:18.41,Default,,0,0,0,,But the students here are such dolts!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:26.20,0:07:29.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been so hot lately, hasn't it?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:29.12,0:07:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The tea's ready.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:31.35,0:07:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:32.17,0:07:36.67,Narrator,,0,0,0,,I'm finally getting used to my work, \Nbut my landlord still baffles me.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:36.67,0:07:39.16,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He always treats me to tea when I come from school
Dialogue: 10,0:07:39.16,0:07:41.81,Narrator,,0,0,0,,but then he tries to push \Nall sorts of antiques on me.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:41.81,0:07:46.21,Narrator,,0,0,0,,First it was a vase, then an ink stone, \Nthen a rather dirty teacup.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:46.21,0:07:47.46,Narrator,,0,0,0,,And today...
Dialogue: 10,0:07:47.46,0:07:48.71,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:49.37,0:07:51.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't it magnificent?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:52.11,0:07:55.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It was painted by Kazan! \NAstonishing, isn't it! {book: then he unrolled a hanging scroll, a traditional-style bird and flower picture, and told me it was painted by a man named Kazan or something like that.}
Dialogue: 10,0:07:56.15,0:07:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Not really.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:58.49,0:08:02.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, how about this.\NYou could have it for just 15 yen!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:02.62,0:08:06.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry, I don't have any extra money.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:06.09,0:08:10.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry about that!\N You can pay me later!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:10.07,0:08:12.41,Default,,0,0,0,,It's rare to find such a valuable piece.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:12.41,0:08:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't let it slip by!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:14.29,0:08:17.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Look! Even if I had extra money, \NI wouldn't throw it away
Dialogue: 10,0:08:17.37,0:08:19.39,Default,,0,0,0,,on some hanging scroll!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:19.39,0:08:22.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, is that so? \NWell, that's too bad.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:22.33,0:08:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,But sooner or later, I'm sure I'll find something that appeals to you.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:38.84,0:08:42.87,Narrator,,0,0,0,,I've started using the hot springs every day, up in Sumida. {there's no such location near matsuyama so idk what it is}
Dialogue: 10,0:08:42.87,0:08:47.04,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Getting there takes ten minutes by train, \Nor about 30 minutes of walking.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:47.72,0:08:50.94,Narrator,,0,0,0,,A small town with nothing to see \Nthat can't hold a candle to Tokyo,
Dialogue: 10,0:08:50.94,0:08:53.05,Narrator,,0,0,0,,but the hot springs are first-rate.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:53.69,0:08:57.48,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The first class bath is about the size of 15 tatami. {lit: the size of 15 tatami; in book: fifteen feet by eighteen - but here one side is clearly longer than the other}
Dialogue: 10,0:08:58.34,0:09:01.06,Narrator,,0,0,0,,There are usually \Nat least ten people using it.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:01.06,0:09:03.20,Narrator,,0,0,0,,But sometimes, there's just me,
Dialogue: 10,0:09:03.76,0:09:07.62,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and when I'm alone, \NI have fun swimming in the bath.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:18.82,0:09:20.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, another bowl of tempura, please!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:23.92,0:09:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:25.40,0:09:26.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Aye.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:27.01,0:09:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you go.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:28.55,0:09:29.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:45.27,0:09:48.27,Default,,0,0,0,,What is so amusing \Nabout someone eating tempura?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:48.27,0:09:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing if it's not over four bowls in one sitting!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:52.27,0:09:53.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Be quiet!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:53.64,0:09:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether I eat four bowls or even five, \Nit's none of your business!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:58.18,0:10:00.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, start the lesson. \NOpen your books to page 25!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:15.63,0:10:20.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this supposed to be funny?\N These are just cowardly jokes.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:20.22,0:10:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It's more cowardly to get mad\N about what you actually did yourself.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:25.39,0:10:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't talk back to me!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:32.15,0:10:35.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't teach anything\N to you conceited idiots!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:41.28,0:10:46.66,Thought,,0,0,0,,I can't believe I left Tokyo \Nto come teach these imbeciles.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:48.63,0:10:54.39,Narrator,,0,0,0,,I was furious, but I felt better after a bath and a night's sleep.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:54.39,0:10:56.30,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The students calmed down too. {lit: acted as if nothing happened}
Dialogue: 10,0:10:57.02,0:11:00.64,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Four days later, I had some dumplings on my way back from the hot springs. {dango}
Dialogue: 10,0:11:01.27,0:11:02.74,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Located near the red-light district,
Dialogue: 10,0:11:02.74,0:11:05.50,Narrator,,0,0,0,,this restaurant has a reputation for being very delicious.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:05.50,0:11:08.31,Narrator,,0,0,0,,I was sure I didn't see any students.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:17.69,0:11:19.90,Narrator,,0,0,0,,I was just speechless.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:20.32,0:11:22.78,Narrator,,0,0,0,,And after that fizzled out,{lit: when I thought dango was over}
Dialogue: 10,0:11:22.78,0:11:27.33,Narrator,,0,0,0,,the red towel I use at the hot springs became the new topic.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:33.21,0:11:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,"No swimming in the bathtub."
Dialogue: 10,0:11:38.76,0:11:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure that no one else \Nswims in the tub.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:41.92,0:11:44.43,Default,,0,0,0,,They must have put\N the sign up just for me.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:53.36,0:11:56.29,Narrator,,0,0,0,,I felt sorry for myself,
Dialogue: 10,0:11:56.29,0:11:58.91,Narrator,,0,0,0,,having to come to a hole-in-the-wall place like this,
Dialogue: 10,0:11:58.91,0:12:00.58,Narrator,,0,0,0,,where everyone knows what you've done. {lit: using the tip of your nose - think he means "everyone is being nosy"}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:00.58,0:12:03.45,Narrator,,0,0,0,,And when I got home,\N I had to deal with this, as usual.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:03.45,0:12:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you, I'm not buying anything.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:29.43,0:12:32.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The rest of the teachers \Nseem to have departed already.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:35.11,0:12:37.61,Default,,0,0,0,,This is your first time\N on night duty, isn't it?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:38.34,0:12:39.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:39.46,0:12:42.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The night duty room \Ngets hot in the afternoon. {lit: is in the setting sun}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:42.08,0:12:44.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You should probably just \Nstay here until dark.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:45.45,0:12:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:47.09,0:12:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The boarding students have been behaving lately,
Dialogue: 10,0:12:49.84,0:12:51.66,Default,,0,0,0,,so you should have \Na peaceful night duty.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:52.22,0:12:55.17,Default,,0,0,0,,As vice principal, you never serve night duty, do you?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:57.02,0:12:58.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It must seem unfair to you,
Dialogue: 10,0:12:58.50,0:13:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,but the principal and I are Imperial appointees. {in the book: When I asked why these two were excused from this obligation, the answer was that they, unlike the rest of us, were directly appointed to their positions by the Prime Minister. }
Dialogue: 10,0:13:01.53,0:13:03.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow, that's great.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:03.34,0:13:04.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It's nothing, really.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:06.10,0:13:10.35,Default,,0,0,0,,By the way, I was hoping \Nto invite you out fishing soon.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:10.35,0:13:11.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Fishing?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:12.90,0:13:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, don't you like to fish?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:14.94,0:13:16.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, in my life,
Dialogue: 10,0:13:16.89,0:13:19.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I only caught three tiny carp\N in a fishpond when I was little,
Dialogue: 10,0:13:19.97,0:13:21.32,Default,,0,0,0,,so I neither like nor hate it.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:23.40,0:13:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Well then, why don't you join us?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:25.59,0:13:27.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll see you later.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:32.03,0:13:34.84,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Red Shirt was acting repulsively pleasant.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:35.86,0:13:39.88,Narrator,,0,0,0,,And being on night duty,\N I had a whole lot of nothing to do,
Dialogue: 10,0:13:42.14,0:13:46.62,Narrator,,0,0,0,,so I left before dusk instead \Nand went to the hot springs.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:57.14,0:13:59.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, I thought you were on night duty.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:59.07,0:14:00.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:00.82,0:14:03.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not a good idea to leave for no reason\N when you're on night duty.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:03.96,0:14:06.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry, nothing happened. \NI'm already on my way back.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:07.49,0:14:12.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You're so negligent. What if the principal or vice principal sees you?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:12.43,0:14:14.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:14.90,0:14:16.15,Default,,0,0,0,,See you later.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:25.49,0:14:27.21,Narrator,,0,0,0,,After I ate dinner, at about 9 PM,
Dialogue: 10,0:14:27.21,0:14:31.06,Narrator,,0,0,0,,I wasn't sleepy yet, but I crawled under the mosquito net
Dialogue: 10,0:14:31.06,0:14:32.39,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and went to bed anyway.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:45.57,0:14:46.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Grasshoppers!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:48.50,0:14:52.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! Get out! You! Take this!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:07.71,0:15:11.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn those rowdy students! \NThey won't get away with this!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:13.56,0:15:16.74,Narrator,,0,0,0,,I immediately called in the boarding students' representatives.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:18.39,0:15:20.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I want a straight answer.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:20.86,0:15:22.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did you put \Ngrasshoppers in my bed?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:23.69,0:15:25.86,Default,,0,0,0,,What's a grasshopper?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:26.40,0:15:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't act dumb!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:28.26,0:15:30.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}This{\i0} is a grasshopper!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:30.15,0:15:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you trying to tell me you've never seen one?!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:34.12,0:15:35.87,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a locust.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:36.43,0:15:38.54,Default,,0,0,0,,A... A locust?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:38.54,0:15:41.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Hell! I don't care what it's called!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:41.63,0:15:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did you plant it in my bed?!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:43.77,0:15:46.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody planted anything, right?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:46.02,0:15:47.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 10,0:15:47.13,0:15:50.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So you didn't, huh? \NThen how did they get here?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:50.68,0:15:53.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Locusts like warm places.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:53.49,0:15:56.14,Default,,0,0,0,,They probably crawled in \Nwhile you were away. {hitori here is "on their own"}
Dialogue: 10,0:15:56.84,0:15:57.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't give me that crap!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:57.89,0:16:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You want me to believe the grasshoppers got in on their own?!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:00.89,0:16:03.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Explain! Why'd you pull such a nasty stunt?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:03.65,0:16:08.65,Default,,0,0,0,,We already told you. None of us did it,\N so there's nothing to explain.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:08.65,0:16:10.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, is that so?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:10.87,0:16:13.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So you've decided to play innocent \Nall the way through?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:13.85,0:16:17.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Fine, then. Still, I feel sorry for you \Nif you can't tell the difference
Dialogue: 10,0:16:17.16,0:16:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,between refined and vulgar behavior even in junior high school. {meaning "in your age"}
Dialogue: 10,0:16:20.11,0:16:21.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Now go, get out of my sight!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:28.65,0:16:31.72,Thought,,0,0,0,,Why did I ever come \Nto this stupid hick town?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:33.50,0:16:35.24,Thought,,0,0,0,,I wonder how Kiyo's doing?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:35.68,0:16:39.68,Thought,,0,0,0,,Looking back now, \NI can't help but admire Kiyo.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:39.68,0:16:42.68,Thought,,0,0,0,,She's just an old woman\N with no status or education,
Dialogue: 10,0:16:42.68,0:16:44.54,Thought,,0,0,0,,but she has a truly noble spirit.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:45.39,0:16:47.19,Thought,,0,0,0,,I suddenly miss her.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:55.07,0:16:56.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn them!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:58.08,0:17:00.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll show them!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:07.99,0:17:10.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop hiding and get out here!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:13.59,0:17:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:16.53,0:17:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You cowards!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:17.84,0:17:19.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Get out here!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:19.20,0:17:20.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Open this door!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:25.85,0:17:27.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Crap. They're making a fool of me!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:36.75,0:17:39.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Dammit. Just you wait!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:41.77,0:17:44.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Fine! We'll have an endurance contest!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:44.97,0:17:47.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll never get past me!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:00.87,0:18:05.78,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Three days later, Red Shirt invited me to go fishing.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:07.24,0:18:09.77,Default,,0,0,0,,What a magnificent pine, up there.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:09.77,0:18:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Indeed!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:11.26,0:18:14.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The trunk is straight and opens like an umbrella.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:14.19,0:18:16.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It might as well be a Turner painting.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:17.22,0:18:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, Turner, you're exactly right!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:20.15,0:18:21.64,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you say, Vice Principal?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:21.64,0:18:26.83,Default,,0,0,0,,From now on, I think we should call that "Turner Island."
Dialogue: 10,0:18:27.30,0:18:29.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I like that.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:29.72,0:18:31.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It would be a perfect scene,
Dialogue: 10,0:18:31.87,0:18:34.34,Default,,0,0,0,,if Madonna was also standing there on that rock.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:34.91,0:18:38.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You shouldn't be talking\N about Madonna.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:40.21,0:18:44.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry, no one can hear us.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:44.19,0:18:46.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you sure you won't join in the fishing?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:46.85,0:18:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Nah. After trying it, I've found\N that I don't like to murder things.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:54.30,0:18:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,"Murder" is a bit of an exaggeration.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:58.50,0:19:00.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Vice Principal, have you decided on the punishment
Dialogue: 10,0:19:00.78,0:19:02.99,Default,,0,0,0,,for the unruly boarding students from the other day?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:03.41,0:19:06.38,Default,,0,0,0,,No, we haven't decided \Non the disciplinary action yet.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:06.38,0:19:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I think we'll call all the staff together\N for a meeting to decide.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:10.93,0:19:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I wish you'd hurry up.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:14.68,0:19:16.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I get mad just thinking about it.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:16.51,0:19:19.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Indeed, that is simply scandalous.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:20.32,0:19:23.68,Default,,0,0,0,,A certain mastermind must've been goading the students on.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:24.17,0:19:25.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh-Who?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:26.26,0:19:29.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you talking about, well, {\i1}him{\i0}?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:29.77,0:19:31.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I certainly am.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:32.62,0:19:34.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is it? What "him"?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:34.94,0:19:37.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, you really don't know?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:37.94,0:19:42.11,Default,,0,0,0,,How could I?! Just tell me who he is!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:42.60,0:19:48.12,Default,,0,0,0,,He drove out your predecessor,\N so I thought you might be next.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:48.86,0:19:52.62,Default,,0,0,0,,My predecessor? \NThen it must be Porcupine. {yama arashi}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:53.15,0:19:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Porcupine?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:54.50,0:19:59.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I see. Hotta does kind\N of look like that, doesn't he?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:59.37,0:20:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You're pretty good with nicknames.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:02.63,0:20:04.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So it {\i1}is {\i0}him!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:04.14,0:20:08.82,Default,,0,0,0,,No, we don't have proof, so I can't really make any accusations.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:08.82,0:20:11.64,Default,,0,0,0,,But I'd advise you to watch your step regardless.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:20.07,0:20:21.32,Default,,0,0,0,,What's this?
Dialogue: 10,0:20:21.32,0:20:23.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Money for the shaved ice.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:24.58,0:20:25.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this a joke?
Dialogue: 10,0:20:26.02,0:20:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to be indebted to you\N for that shaved ice. Take it!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:29.91,0:20:33.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll take it, all right. \NBut what brought this on? {/why now}
Dialogue: 10,0:20:33.41,0:20:36.54,Default,,0,0,0,,What difference does it make?!\N I refuse to owe you anything.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:40.27,0:20:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I have news for you too!\N You'd better find new lodgings!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:44.63,0:20:46.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Find new lodgings?
Dialogue: 10,0:20:46.93,0:20:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It's none of your damn business\N where I choose to live!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:50.29,0:20:52.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm afraid it {\i1}is{\i0} my business.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:52.34,0:20:56.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Yesterday, Ikagin asked me\N to get you off his property.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:56.62,0:21:00.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I was shocked, but I found out he was perfectly justified.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:01.28,0:21:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,What did he tell you?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:04.29,0:21:06.95,Default,,0,0,0,,He said you've got some nerve.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:06.95,0:21:09.12,Default,,0,0,0,,He said you made a pass at his wife!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:09.76,0:21:13.62,Default,,0,0,0,,M-Me? I did no such thing!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:14.06,0:21:16.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Your landlord, however, says you did.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:16.12,0:21:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I get it.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:17.28,0:21:20.70,Default,,0,0,0,,He wants me to leave,\N so he made up some lies.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:20.70,0:21:24.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Shame on you for recommending him!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:24.11,0:21:25.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Who should be ashamed?!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:25.48,0:21:27.95,Default,,0,0,0,,What's worse: a bad recommendation or adultery?!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:29.14,0:21:35.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Please don't hesitate to drop by\N whenever you're in the neighborhood!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:40.06,0:21:41.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:41.92,0:21:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. Where to?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:43.61,0:21:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know just yet.\N Follow me for now.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:48.61,0:21:49.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Aye.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:08.68,0:22:13.55,Narrator,,0,0,0,,As I wandered around looking for lodging,\N the sky turned to twilight.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:14.93,0:22:17.58,Narrator,,0,0,0,,I began to feel very lonely.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.84,0:22:37.45,Song,,0,0,0,,I write a letter to my loved one
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.45,0:22:44.64,Song,,0,0,0,,I write and tear it, tear it, and write again
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.64,0:22:51.21,Song,,0,0,0,,I throw the rolled up paper at the window {meaning at the glass, probably as a distraction}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.21,0:22:58.19,Song,,0,0,0,,It's raining outside, just like the tears on my cheeks
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.46,0:23:06.29,Song,,0,0,0,,Life is a sea, youth is a boat
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.29,0:23:13.33,Song,,0,0,0,,My love, please come and save me
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.33,0:23:15.47,Song,,0,0,0,,S.O.S.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.63,0:23:19.51,Song,,0,0,0,,S.O.S.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.51,0:23:27.10,Song,,0,0,0,,I feel like I'm sinking
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.10,0:23:36.54,Song,,0,0,0,,Not a single star in sight, in the sea of ​​sadness
